The RES Strategy sets the targets on the use of renewable energy sources and the manners for attaining these targets, in particular:
* potential  of renewable energy sources;
* feasibility of the use of renewable energy sources;
* target volume and dynamics for increasing the share of electricity from renewable energy sources and share of biofuels in the gross final energy consumption; as well as the share of biofuels in the total consumption of fuels for transport; and,
* incentives for the use of renewable energy sources.

The incentives shall include in particular:
* investment support;
* tax credits;

The incentives shall include in particular:
* investment support;
* tax credits;
* obligation of the electricity suppliers on purchasing electricity generated from renewable energy sources and obligation on mandatory placing on the market of blends of fossil fuels with biofuels;
* issuing guarantees of electricity origin;
* feed-in tariffs for the purchase of electricity generated from RES that obtain status of a preferential producer; or
* increased prices for the consumers, as regards the use of energy from renewable sources.

The funds required to implement the incentives referred to in paragraph (3) of this Article can be provided, inter alia, from:
* the Budget of the Republic of Macedonia;
* grants, donations and sponsorships;
* loans; or
* state aid pursuant to the law.

